# UI Library Requirements Analysis

This document provides a comprehensive 360-degree analysis of UI library requirements for the Mileage Management System (MMS). Use this to evaluate and select the best UI library/design system for the project.

---

## 1. Project Context

### 1.1 Application Type
- **Progressive Web App (PWA)** with offline capability
- **Enterprise B2B** application for railway maintenance planning
- **Data-heavy dashboards** with complex visualizations
- **Multi-role access** (Admin, Planner, Operator, Viewer)

### 1.2 Tech Stack Constraints
- **Framework:** Astro + React 19
- **Runtime:** Bun.js
- **Styling approach:** Open (CSS-in-JS, Tailwind, or CSS Modules)
- **Bundle size:** Critical (PWA, may work on tablets in workshops)

### 1.3 User Profiles
| Role | Device | Environment | Technical Level |
|------|--------|-------------|-----------------|
| Planner | Desktop | Office | Medium-High |
| Operator | Tablet/Desktop | Workshop/Office | Low-Medium |
| Manager | Desktop/Mobile | Office/Remote | Medium |
| Admin | Desktop | Office | High |

