## 7. Evaluation Criteria

When evaluating libraries, score each on:

| Criterion | Weight | Description |
|-----------|--------|-------------|
| **Component completeness** | 25% | Has all essential components |
| **Data table quality** | 20% | Critical component excellence |
| **Visual design** | 15% | Professional, modern appearance |
| **Performance** | 15% | Bundle size, runtime |
| **DX & TypeScript** | 10% | Developer experience |
| **Accessibility** | 10% | WCAG compliance |
| **Ecosystem health** | 5% | Maintenance, community |

### 7.1 Minimum Viable Criteria

A library must meet ALL of these to be considered:
- [ ] React 19 compatible
- [ ] SSR/Astro compatible
- [ ] TypeScript support
- [ ] Active maintenance (commits in last 3 months)
- [ ] Data table component with sorting/filtering/pagination
- [ ] Form components (inputs, selects, date pickers)
- [ ] Modal/dialog component
- [ ] Professional appearance

