## 8. Libraries to Evaluate

Suggested libraries to research (in no particular order):

### Comprehensive UI Libraries
- **shadcn/ui** - Radix primitives + Tailwind, copy-paste model
- **Radix UI** - Headless primitives, maximum flexibility
- **Chakra UI** - Good DX, accessible, styled
- **Mantine** - Feature-rich, good data components
- **Ant Design** - Enterprise-focused, comprehensive
- **MUI (Material UI)** - Most popular, Google design
- **Ariakit** - Accessible primitives
- **NextUI** - Modern, Tailwind-based

### Data Table Specific
- **TanStack Table** - Headless, most flexible
- **AG Grid** - Most powerful, but heavy
- **React Table** - Predecessor to TanStack

### Chart Libraries (Separate Evaluation)
- **Chart.js** - Current choice
- **Recharts** - React-native
- **Visx** - Low-level, D3-based
- **Nivo** - Feature-rich

